utf8casestr is unsafe regarding length if input strings and should have a variant with size limits 

A possibly simple adjustment is this where utf8codepoint gets a size limit which makes the string end directly
```

const utf8_int8_t*
utf8codepoint_safe(const utf8_int8_t* str,
                   utf8_int32_t* out_codepoint, const utf8_int8_t* str_end)
{
	if (str >= str_end) {
		*out_codepoint = 0;
		return str_end;
	}
	return utf8codepoint(str, out_codepoint);
}
```

Then replace all calls of utf8codepoint with utf8codepoint_safe and provide haystack_end and needle_end accordingly.

